{
  "texts": [
    "The vertical gray shaded region corresponds to the 2018 April 21 measurements, and the vertical un-shaded region corresponds to the 2018 April 25 measurements.",
    "The brightness asymmetry A is ∼0.2-0.4, indicating an asymmetric ring-like structure.",
    "Moreover, the fractional central brightness f C is ∼0-0.5, indicating a clear central depression.",
    "Comparing the extracted features between April 21 and April 25 is challenging due to the lack of Top Set images for DIFMAP, eht-imaging, and SMILI on April 25 bands 1 and 2 as well as the sparser (u, v) coverage on April 25 leading to higher uncertainty.",
    "For the available measurements, the features look consistent within their errors between days."
  ]
}